snippet.textDisplay: I think this is the most sedate (not boring, to be sure... just quiet) "Bond" theme ever. It will be interesting to see how it does on the charts. I guess we'll all see how it fares with the listening public.

snippet.textDisplay:
If they made new Special Agent Oso episodes, I have a few ideas for references to James Bond 007 titles and singing voices for Paw Pilot when she sings the codename song:
1. Dr. Sew (Dr. No (Singing voice for Paw Pilot in codename song: normal voice, Meghan Strange))
2. For Santa with Love (From Russia with Love (Singing voice for Paw Pilot in codename song: Michael Buble in the style of Matt Monro))
3. Phone Ringer (Goldfinger (Singing voice for Paw Pilot in codename song: Shirley Bassey))
4. Thundersplash (Thunderball (Singing voice for Paw Pilot in codename song: Tom Jones))
5. You Only Brush Twice (You Only Live Twice (Singing voice for Paw Pilot in codename song: Nancy Sinatra))
6. We Have All the Food From the Market (We Have All the Time in the World from On Her Majesty's Secret Service (Singing voice for Paw Pilot in codename song: Jamie Foxx in the style of Louis Armstrong))
7. Weddings Are Forever (Diamonds Are Forever (Singing voice for Paw Pilot in codename song: Shirley Bassey))
8. Live and Not Lie (Live and Let Die (Singing voice for Paw Pilot in codename song: Paul McCartney))
9. The Kid with the Winter Coat (The Man with the Golden Gun (Singing voice for Paw Pilot in codename song: Lulu))
10. Nobody Bakes it Better (Nobody Does it Better from The Spy Who Loved Me (Singing voice for Paw Pilot in codename song: Carly Simon))
11. Moon Spotter (Moonraker (Singing voice for Paw Pilot in codename song: Shirley Bassey))
12. For Your Cat Only (For Your Eyes Only (Singing voice for Paw Pilot in codename song: Sheena Easton))
13. Octopuppy (Octopussy (Singing voice for Paw Pilot in codename song: Rita Coolidge))
14. A View to a Television (A View to a Kill (Singing voice for Paw Pilot in codename song: Simon Le Bon of Duran Duran))
15. The Living Train Tracks (The Living Daylights (Singing voice for Paw Pilot in codename song: Morten Harket of A-ha))
16. License to Sing (License to Kill (Singing voice for Paw Pilot in codename song: Gladys Knight))
17. Golden Fries (GoldenEye (Singing voice for Paw Pilot in codename song: Tina Turner))
18. Tomorrow Always Works (Tomorrow Never Dies (Singing voice for Paw Pilot in codename song: Sheryl Crow))
